HEADWORD: Amphipneust
<hw>Am*phip"neust</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'amfi`</grk> + <?/ one who breathes, <?/ to breathe.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of a tribe of Amphibia, which have both
lungs and gills at the same time, as the proteus and siren.</def>⟦br⟧
